intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Describe the main components of a computer system;
Describe the concepts of digital representation, bits and words;
Work with the binary and two's complement representation of numbers and convert between these and decimal numbers;
Explain how the behaviours of signed and unsigned operations are caused by the underlying representation;
Describe of how basic control constructs and algorithms are translated to machine language;
Compare critically two machine architectures at the instructions set level;
Describe the central functions of an operating system;
Describe how virtual memory works, together with its benefits and limitations;
Describe how end systems and routers are connected in the Internet;
Explain the main levels of abstraction in computer networks.
